                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3j38m41r/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>at the same time the subjoined nos of the<lb/>\n                <sic>occident</sic> which I require to complete<lb/> *my pyle—Except 3, they are all\n                of<lb/> the weekly series and failed to reach<lb/> me through irregularity of the\n                Post Office</p>\n            <list type=\"simple\">\n                <head/>\n                <item>Vol 14 nos 1,2.</item>\n                <item rend=\"indent(1)\"> 15 no 5.</item>\n                <item rend=\"indent(1)\"> 17 nos 23, 25, 26, 28, 31, 43.</item>\n                <item rend=\"indent(1)\"> 18 nos 6, 12, 40, 41, 47, 49, 51</item>\n            </list>\n            <p>You can send them by mail—the weeklies<lb/> can go in one wrapper.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">In a recent letter you ask<lb/> whether something can't be done\n                with<lb/> the <persName>Benjamins</persName>. I before wrote you<lb/> enclose your\n                account and I will<lb/> do what I can with <persName>Wm Benjamin</persName><lb/>\n                here. You also are surprised<lb/> that your subscribers here are, so few, but\n                    <add>בעה\"ר</add> Jews don't<lb/> increase in <placeName>Canada</placeName>. If\n                you have<lb/> no field here, be comforted with<lb/> the reflection that neither have\n                I</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3j38m41r/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
